# pyProbe

pyProbe is a Python-based application designed for acquisition of autofluorescence lifetime data using the TimeTagger Ultra from Swabbian Instruments

## Changes

Last updated on 2026-01-09 by João Lagarto

## Features

- Laser intensity and frequency control via Harp (use with Becker and Hickl GmbH lasers)
- Data acquisition in two detection channels using the TimeTagger Ultra (Swabbian Instruments)
    - Real time monitoring of input events (detectors, lasers, and external trigger)
    - Control of curve settings, such as temporal offset, number of bins and bin width
    - Adjustable acquisition time

- Integration with Spinnaker for integration with FLIR cameras
    - Adjustable exposure time
    - Software and Hardware trigger

- Detector ON/OFF control (SPADs from Hamamatsu)
- NeoPixel LED right control of state and brightness.
- Multiple data acquisition modes
    - single-point measurements without i2maging
    - imaging with real-time tracking
    - imaging with real-time tracking and tracing of last 500 measurements
    - imaging with real-time tracking, tracing and visible ROI

